reviews.review_text:
bust bummer Listen to the intro - Ramrod's bust clearly has the band bummed. That's my take after the low-energy Bertha, at least.

So while I'll stick out the stream (autumn '71 is one of my favorite Dead eras), it doesn't look like I'll be downloading or burning this "low gen" recording.

But check out the set list. They didn't short-change the audience. That's professionalism.

And I love Jerry's message after the first set: "Everything's gonna be alright."
